libgrapple
------------------------------------------
Grapple is designed to be a simple network layer, allowing the addition of
multiplayer features to a game (or other application) for as little as a dozen
lines of code. However it is also fully featured, so if you want more from
your networking, you can have it.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.9-1
  libgrapple-devel-0.9.8-1bl3
  libgrapple0.9_2-0.9.8-1bl3
  libssl3-3.5.6-1
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-3
  automake-20250528-1
  binutils-2.46-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  libssl-devel-3.5.6-1
  libtool-2.5.4-1
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://www.libgrapple.net/

Canonical download:
  https://www.libgrapple.net/downloads/libgrapple-0.9.8.tbz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libgrapple-0.9.8-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libgrapple-0.9.8-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libgrapple-0.9.8-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libgrapple-0.9.8-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libgrapple0.9_2-0.9.8-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libgrapple-devel-0.9.8-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

